<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-671] surefire should not run abstract test cases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-671</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Surefire reports a failure if an abstract test case (extending junit.framework.TestCase) with TestCase in its name contains no tests. This bug appears to have the same symptoms as issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-221&quot; title=&quot;surefire should not run abstract test cases&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-221&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-221&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but as it&apos;s so old I&apos;m assuming a different cause&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround: adding @Ignore to the abstract test case (or change the class name)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
